00:02:34.512 --> 00:02:38.475
There has been one very important
step in sleep and dream research.

00:02:38.475 --> 00:02:44.230
That was the discovery of paradoxical
(REM) sleep by Michel Jouvet

00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:47.524
and others in the 1950s and early 1960s.

00:02:47.524 --> 00:02:53.576
And indeed that one finding
somewhat revolutionised this area,

00:02:53.576 --> 00:02:58.241
since a link was soon made between
paradoxical sleep and dreaming.

00:02:58.241 --> 00:03:02.166
Michel Jouvet's legacy has been
really important and inspirational.

00:03:02.166 --> 00:03:05.738
I have had the opportunity to talk
with him, and show him my new results.

00:03:05.738 --> 00:03:13.141
He retains a freshness and youthful
spirit that is quite amazing.

00:03:13.454 --> 00:03:18.578
He has spent a very large part of his
life recording his dreams in the morning,

00:03:18.578 --> 00:03:21.354
transcribing them either
in writing or in drawings.

00:03:21.354 --> 00:03:25.666
It is a collection of dreams that is altogether
valuable for a whole lot of reasons,

00:03:25.666 --> 00:03:29.920
aesthetic as well as
artistic and scientific.

